    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>I give you many thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> obliging favor. I have
                    just sent <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0209">the map</title></bibl> to
                    <persName ref="pe0006">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Bailey</persName> with some
                    corrections. I hope by February it will be fit to deliver to the public. You are
                    very kind in y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> offer of prints but beg you would
                    not put y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>self to any expence. My right wrist which
                    is the only part much affected by my fall is quite well. I take my children to
                    School on Monday which will occasion another <sic>months</sic>. after which I
                    shall set quiet the whole winter. Let me hear from you on my return as y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Letters are always grateful to</p>
                <closer><salute>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Oct<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi>
                        27<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> 1776.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> <persName ref="pe0228">George Paton</persName></addrLine>
                    </address></p>
                <p>17/6</p>
            </div>
        </body>
